      "Just to add more data - we have 5 nodes w/ 256G of RAM.   \r\nWe have systematically lowered the cache by 5G on each node until it quits swapping during a normal day of usage.  We started all of them at 128G of cache (1/2 available RAM)\r\n2 of the nodes have stopped swapping with the cache set to 60G\r\n3 of the nodes continue to swap and their cache is set to 40G\r\nwe have ~40 tables -- a dozen of those have >10 million rows  -- 2 have > 100 million\r\nwrite usage is pretty constant throughout the day at around 5k w/s with reads jumping from 0 to 100k/s\r\n\r\nThis has been ongoing with 2.3.4 -- 2.3.4 w/ modified GC - and now 2.3.5 which we upgraded to last night.\r\n\r\nUbuntu 14.04.1 - Rethink 2.3.5 from official apt source - 256G RAM / 24 dual core cpus"
